    "narrative": "The Austin Waves are primed for a high-ceiling offensive output today, headlined by **Kyle Tucker** (81.94) and **Gunnar Henderson** (81.88). Both players benefit from favorable matchups against mid-rotation arms and projected wind blowing out, providing a premium lift to their base projections. **Luis Robert Jr.** (77.40) also stands out as an elite play; despite the park downgrade, his 19% SP skill advantage against the lefty Prielipp creates a massive platoon-neutralizing floor for stolen base and power production. We are leaning heavily on **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** (73.66) and **Jackson Merrill** (75.27) as secondary engines, both of whom possess favorable lineup positioning and exploitable pitching matchups that push their efficiency well into the \"Strong\" start tier.\n\nThe most difficult decision on today\u2019s card was leaving **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (58.68) on the bench. While his xwOBA profile remains strong, the optimizer docked his score due to a neutral platoon disadvantage and a lack of elite sprint speed\u2014a critical factor given our aggressive prioritization of the stolen base category. He fell just short of the 60.00 threshold required to displace **Marcell Ozuna** (59.52) or **Andy Pages** (62.35), the latter of whom maintains value through his spot in a favorable lineup context despite a slight penalty for facing an elite defensive catcher. \n\nWe are closely monitoring the environment for the remainder of the roster, as the lack of elite-level arms (xERA < 3.00) in today's matchups bodes well for a productive Roto day. **Liam Hicks** (44.89) remains our most marginal start; while he is currently active, his reliance on a dynamic platoon edge is the primary factor keeping him above our bench threshold. We are comfortable with the current configuration, provided no late-breaking lineup scratches impact **Drake Baldwin** or **Miguel Vargas**, both of whom are projected to anchor the bottom of our start-worthy cohort.",
